    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"422703\">Malvin Gattinger</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113488-general/topic/Proving.20termination.20with.20List.2EShortlex/near/548022826\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Yes, I also would have guessed there should be a <code>Nat.lt_wf</code> (without <code>Rel</code>) <span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Although if it was not Nat, getting from an existing <code>WellFoundedRelation</code> typeclass instance to a <code>WellFounded</code> assumption still feels a little more complicated than it should be...</p>",
